([nil nil ((#("It is midday.

The rain got lighter.

The insects that went underground started crawling out of the ground in swarms.

Chill breeze blew through the forest.

Haider had been calmed by Mallory's and Ichabod's words.

He had found a newer way of looking at scenarios and events that would occur around him.

He felt indebted to Ichabod and Mallory.

Regarding his doubts about his actions, he now understood the reasons and justifications behind his actions.

He thought, No matter what the circumstances are from here on out. I'll not take actions based on my feelings alone. I need to have a concrete understanding of what I'm doing.

He now understood very well that his actions were justified, even though they were carried out by the means of his own hatred towards that man. But still justified.

He was a hypocrite.

A liar.

With a twisted sense of right and wrong.

He had to be killed, otherwise he would've become a hindrance for him.

Even if Haider were to have evaded him, he would've become a reason of hardship for someone else.

Haider raised his head and looked forward.

He saw Mallory and Ichabod standing together and talking to each other outside of the tree's shade.

Faint sunlight passing through the blockade of clouds, falling on them, giving them a warm presence, with light rain falling frequently with delays in between.

Haider stood in the shade of the tree, looking at them with his big eyes, wide open.

As if he was envious of them.

Throughout Haider's life, he only knew the love of his own mother. He didn't understood friendship, fellowship, or rivalry.

When He looked at the two of them, He sensed a feel of loneliness.

Haider thought to himself, Thanks to them, now I know what I was feeling and what was troubling me. He felt like an outsider watching two strangers talking to each other. Discussing ideas and feelings openly without any hesitation or embarrassment.

He kept glaring at them, Could I ever be this open with someone? Could I ever feel as if I were included along with them?

No matter how one look at it. Haider was strong, but sentimental, and above all still a child.

He felt like the child that is being kept out of the playground where rest of the children are playing, laughing, and cheering for each other.

It was not their fault. They didn't do it intentionally. It was his fault for being so fixated on one thing that he lost the sight of everything and everyone around him.

He was so consumed in the hatred for the person who was the cause behind his mother's death, that he didn't care about the repercussions of his actions.

But not caring is just the front that he setup.

Internally, he was tearing himself apart.

The more he indulged with the thought of hating someone, the more he made himself feel detached from everyone else.

Humans are different. Each and everyone have their own lives, their own goals, and motivations.

In order to find meaning in their lives, they try to find people who value them.

But if one is so absorbed by their own goals, and rejects what the people around them values, then that person is left alone.

Nobody wants to stick around people who do not value them.

Haider understood this. To be specific, he understood this feeling recently.

That is why this feeling of solitude overtook him.

He looked into himself and only found dark murky fluid of hatred. He didn't sympathize with Ichabod and Mallory. He understood them but never try to feel them.

He felt guilty of this.

He wanted to approach them and thank them the right way.

But he was reluctant.

His eyes slowly moved down, staring at the ground. His head slowly tilted downward.

I'll leave the moment we find the sorcerer. I'll protect them and fight whenever the need arises. That's the least I can do to repay them.

But then he heard someone call him by his name.

\"Haider. Come on let's go.\"

Haider lifter his head and saw Mallory looking at him with a soft smile calling him out.

Ichabod was also looking at him, with his usual sharp glare.

\"Come on! What are you doing there standing all by yourself? Let's go before the rain starts again.\" Mallory said to him.

Haider kept looking at the two of them for a while.

Then he slowly walked towards them. \"What's the matter?\" Ichabod asked in a calm tone.

Haider let out a sweet warm smile, as he said, \"Nothing... And thanks by the way... For earlier... You know\"

Mallory and Ichabod were shocked at the scene.

Mallory was lost for words, since it has been more than a week that has passed since they were traveling together, but Haider had never smiled.

Ichabod also felt the same way.

But amongst the three Ichabod was the most emotionally mature and understood the intentions and emotions of the people around him.

Ichabod also gave a warm smile, since he understood that Haider was now being genuine, \"No problems. Whenever you need us, we'll be there for you.\"

They continued on their quest, that was to find the magician and ask the magician to get rid of both Ichabod's and Mallory's disease.

They continued their journey. On the way they faced many more hardships.

Sometimes their were dens of wild dogs, sometimes they would encounter a wild bear, and even large snakes.

But luckily they would evade them due to Haider's strong sense of smell and awareness of his surroundings.

Right now, at this very moment, Haider had but one goal, it was not to think about revenge or getting stronger, but be active and try his best to locate danger and evade it.

His senses were extremely sharp and active, pinpointing rustles and even slight sounds that Ichabod and Mallory could hardly hear.

Haider would pick them up and would be on guard.

And moreover, they had gotten extremely close.

....

It's night.

Mallory had fallen asleep, Ichabod and Haider were awake.

Both of them stood right next to eachother. Ichabod was taller but thinner than Haider.

Half moon was present and floating in the night sky. It wasn't as bright as the full moon, but still it had enough light that it would make things visible.

Both Ichabod and Haider were sitting right next to each other. Their shadows adjacent to each other fell on the skinny physique of Mallory.

Haider was on night watch, even though he was tired from actively being on guard throughout the day but he was serious about it.

Ichabod had noticed this, since that day, he has been pushing himself, being extra careful and alert.

\"Hey are you alright.\", Ichabod said, \"if you're tired you can go to sleep, I'll wake you up if I sense something unusual.\"

\"No it's alright. I'm fine.\", Haider said with a straight face, but his eyes responded differently.

There were eye-bags beneath them, and he had his eyes squinted, as if he was forcefully trying to keep them open.

Ichabod noticing it said, \"You don't need to push yourself like this. Have pity for yourself as well as you pity us.\"

Haider remained silent, as he looked at Ichabod. Ichabod then continued, \"If your this tired that your forcing yourself to stay up. What if a problem did occur, then you'd be too tired to fight. Would that be a favorable outcome?\"

Haider listened and replied, \"Okay\" as he laid down.

Different types of insect were chirping and giving life to this dense forest.

\"Even though the chirping of crickets is quite annoying and makes it hard to fall asleep but even that is something that necessary don't you think?\" Ichabod said.

Haider replied, \"Yeah, this forest would feel like a haunted place without them. Even if something is troublesome at the moment, it would make the environment feel empty with its absence.\"

Ichabod said with a smile, \"Yeah, you're right. Sometimes I feel what if we were to get rid of this disease, how will it feel then? Would we feel its absence? Will it sadden us? Or give us joy?\"

As Ichabod stared at the sky, some stars were visible, some were hidden by the leaves of the tree and said,

\"They say life is a test, but what if we overcome this test, wouldn't it be logical to think a trial even worse than this will befall us.\"

Haider, who was also staring at the starts, the vast sky, and the leaves and branches of the tree, turned his head and looked at Ichabod, he looked sad.

As if grief had overtaken him.

Ichabod also turned his head towards Haider, his frown turned into a warm smile, as he said, \"I guess we won't know that for now.\"

\"Throughout our lives we've dealt with this disease, we visited different doctors...\" He stopped for a moment, and then continued, \"well I was taken to the doctors.\"

\"My parents never cared that much about Mallory since she is a girl. People of our village values boys a lot. To them we represent strength.\"

\"So I can't even imagine the disappointment they felt, when they heard the news that I can't be cured.\"

Ichabod then said with a sigh, as he looked at Haider in his eyes, \"No matter, whatever happens, even if there is a moment when you're in a situation where you would have to choose between who to save first, promise me, that you'll choose Mallory.\"

Haider looking straight into Ichabod's eyes, he felt Ichabod's sincerity, his strong feelings for his young sister, to which Haider replied with a reassuring tone, \"I promise, that I'll protect her no matter what.\"

When hearing Haider's response, Ichabod gave out a warm smile, and he said, \"Thanks, my friend.\"
